# Phase 4 — Memory Layer Verification

These screenshots were captured after Phase 4 end-to-end verification, when
the Flink CEP job (Phase 3) was feeding pattern matches through the Kafka
consumer into the Graphiti knowledge graph (Phase 4) for the first time.

At capture time the graph contained:
- 111 Episodic nodes (natural-language episode summaries)
- 93 typed PatternOccurrence entities (extracted by the LLM via the
  prescribed ontology)
- 1 Pattern entity (ThermalVibrationCascade)
- 1 Machine entity (Machine-03)
- 615 relationships total (329 MENTIONS + 286 RELATES_TO)

Both visuals show the institutional memory built up from a single
simulator run with a cascade injection on Machine-03.

## machine03_hero.png

Focused subgraph showing Machine-03 at the center, connected to 20
neighboring episodes and PatternOccurrence entities through MENTIONS
edges. Generated by limiting the result to 20 records for visual clarity.

Cypher query used:

```cypher
MATCH (m:Machine {name: "Machine-03"})<-[r1:MENTIONS]-(e:Episodic)-[r2:MENTIONS]->(po:PatternOccurrence)
RETURN m, e, po, r1, r2
LIMIT 20
```

This is the "structure is real" visual: the radial layout makes the
hub-and-spoke topology of per-machine memory immediately legible.

## full_graph_scale.png

The full unconstrained graph view — all 207 nodes and 615 relationships
in one frame. Machine-03 sits at the dense center; episode and
PatternOccurrence nodes radiate outward.

Cypher query used:

```cypher
MATCH (n) RETURN n
```

This is the "scale is real" visual: the density confirms a single
machine over a short period of simulated time produces substantial
queryable memory.